parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The collapse or sagging of the seat can cause the driver to be unable to see over the wheel or reach the acceleration and brake pedals, which can lead to accidents or make it difficult to operate the vehicle safely. Additionally, the airbag light may come on due to the collapsed seat either cutting the airbag electrical cable or puncturing the airbag itself.
symptoms: making it difficult to see over the wheel or reach the acceleration and brake pedals
and the airbag light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat suspension mat can cause the seat cushion to sag, making it difficult to operate the vehicle safely.

pushing the driver forward out of the safety of the side seat bolsters.
